<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY: 

This action would modify the official description of the Class D airspace associated with the Cherry Capital Airport,
Traverse City, Michigan, by adding the phrase: ``This Class D airspace area is effective during the specific dates
and times established in advance by a Notice to Airmen. The effective date and time will thereafter be continuously
published in the Airport Facility Director.'' On September 18, 1993, Airspace Reclassification discontinued the
use of the terms ``control zone'' and ``airport traffic area.'' Airspace designated from the surface for an airport
where there is an operating control tower is now Class D airspace. The intended effect of this action is to allow a variation
of Class D airspace effective times to coincide with the operating hours of the Traverse City, Michigan, Airport Traffic
Control Tower at Cherry Capital Airport.



