small volume builders who may have a more difficult time implementing the regulations and making the necessary calculations
to determine the check digit. When using simple arithmetic, those calculations may take as long as 15 minutes per vessel.
The Coast Guard has developed a computer program which calculates the check digit which is available to any vessel
manufacturer with a computer. The Coast Guard has also developed several work sheets to help determine the HIN for
a vessel and the worksheets are also available. Therefore, preliminary analysis indicates that a 19 character HIN
will not have a significant economic impact on a substantial number of small entities.


