samples to determine species, length, weight, age, sex composition of catch, and predator-prey interactions; or
any other information needed to manage the fisheries. They may collect data on marine mammals, seabirds, and other
species as appropriate. Information obtained from observers would also be used to monitor compliance with fishing
and related regulations. 

The Regional Director would review fishery monitoring programs and report to the Council on methods to improve data
